In this section, AChoir has parsed information about Run and RunOnce Registry Keys. These are THE MOST common Registry keys where malicious programs(MalWare) can reside. These Registry keys allow malware to PERSIST across system reboots. These Registry Keys can also be used for legitimate software and utilities. Some good indicators that Run Keys are being used maliciously is if they run programs that have random file names, or are installed/run from Temp Directories. Focus on both the file names, and where the programs are located to determine if they look suspicious.
